The valuation of Group's financial instruments was a key area of focus of our audit due to the degree of complexity involved in valuing some of the instruments and the significance of the judgments and estimates made by management.

As of December 31, 2017, the Group‘s financial instruments that were carried at fair value are derivative ﬁnancial asset and its investment in Swank Venture Limited classified as availabIe-for- sale financial asset. In addition, the Group has investment in Nevaeh Limited classified as available-for—sale financial asset accounted at cost.

Valuation of Vessels Refer to Note 11‘ Fixed Assets'

Management has estimated the fair value of the Group‘s vessels to be USS 29.6 million as of December 31. 2017 with a revaluation loss in 2017 debited to other comprehensive income amounting to US$ 4.7 million and reversal of impairment loss credited to profit or loss amountrng to US$ 6804 thousand. The management engaged an lndependent appraiser to revalue its vessels.

We challenged and evaluated the appropriateness of the valuation methodologies. and the reasonableness of key estimates and assumptions used by management in determining the fair value and impairment of the Group's investments.

We did not identify any material exceptions from the audit work performed and we found that the valuation methodologies, key estimates and assumptions used by management for the valuation of financial instruments were in line with our expectations, after considering the new information which resulted to restatement as discussed in Note 39 to the consolidated financial statements,

We also evaluated management‘s sensitivity analysis to assess the impact on fair value of these investments and found them to be appropriate

We evaluated the independent appraisers' competence, capabilities and objectivity. We also assessed the appropriateness of methodologies used‘ There were no significant issues noted.

We evaluated the reasonableness of the key estimates and assumptions used In the valuation report and found them to be in line wlth our expectations.
